description:
Talented and versatile, Christian McBride is one of the best jazz bassists around. The product of a musical family, he started his education by focusing on the popular music of his youth. When he was introduced to jazz, he launched into earnest exploration of its many different styles. By learning a number of different musical styles, McBride opened himself up to playing with any other musician he might be paired with, which was key to his success.

Read the blog: http://blogs.jwpepper.com/index.php/jazz-100-christian-mcbride-and-the-future-of-jazz?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=youtube&utm_campaign=jazz100-blogs&utm_content=mcbride-video1
